🌳 What is DOM?

DOM = Document Object Model

It means:
👉 The browser converts your HTML page into a tree of objects
👉 JavaScript can read and change that tree

Example HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
  <h1 id="title">Hello</h1>
  <p>Welcome</p>
</body>
</html>


Browser converts it into structure like:

Document
 └── html
      └── body
           ├── h1
           └── p

This structure = DOM

## Simple definition
  DOM = HTML page as JavaScript objects

So JS can:

✔ change text
✔ change color
✔ hide/show elements
✔ add/remove elements

🎯 Why DOM is needed

Without DOM → JS cannot touch HTML

With DOM → JS controls webpage

Example:
document.getElementById("title").innerText = "Hi Sudarshan";
Page changes instantly ✅

🔑 Main DOM object
Everything starts from:
document
It represents whole webpage.